BT /F2 24 Tf 54 726 Td (locallm-assist in First Principles) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 692 Td (This project is a small command-line agent that lets a local language model answer real) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 677 Td (user questions more truthfully by giving it a minimal, explicit way to call a few tools.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 658 Td (The one-sentence summary is simple: if a local model is missing current facts or exact) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 643 Td (real-world data, the cheapest reliable fix is not a larger framework; it is a tight loop) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 628 Td (where the model can either answer directly or request one concrete tool call, then) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 613 Td (answer from the returned evidence.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 584 Td (1. Start From the Actual Problem) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 562 Td (The core user outcome is simple: type a request into a CLI and get a useful answer back) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 547 Td (from a locally hosted model. That sounds easy until the request depends on fresh or) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 532 Td (precise information.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 513 Td (A raw local model has three predictable weaknesses:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 494 Td (- It does not know current weather, current time, or recent web information unless that) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70 479 Td (data is fetched at runtime.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 462 Td (- It can hallucinate tool usage or facts if the protocol is vague.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 445 Td (- It performs worse when prompts grow long, especially on smaller local models with) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70 430 Td (tighter context budgets.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 413 Td (From first principles, the project therefore does not need a giant agent platform. It) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 398 Td (needs the smallest system that can do four things reliably:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 379 Td (- Accept an explicit user request from the command line.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 362 Td (- Let the model either answer or ask for a tool in a machine-checkable format.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 345 Td (- Execute that tool safely and return structured results.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 328 Td (- Keep the loop bounded so a local model does not drift, bloat the prompt, or spin) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70 313 Td (forever.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 286 Td (2. Facts, Constraints, and Deleted Assumptions) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 264 Td (Facts in the repo:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 245 Td (- The entrypoint is src/main.ts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 228 Td (- The runtime agent loop is in src/agent.ts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 211 Td (- The model client talks to an OpenAI-style chat endpoint in src/llm.ts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 194 Td (- Tools are modular under src/tools/.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 177 Td (- The current built-in tools are weather, web search, and current date/time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 160 Td (Real constraints:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 141 Td (- The model is local, so latency and context size matter more than in large hosted) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70 126 Td (systems.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 109 Td (- Fresh facts must come from external services at runtime.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 92 Td (- The model must be forced into a narrow output contract or the loop becomes brittle.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 75 Td (- Prompt growth must stay bounded because token counting is only estimated, not exact.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 498 28 Td (Page 1 of 5) Tj ET
