BT /F1 11 Tf 54 736 Td (The project also deliberately deletes a few bad defaults:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 717 Td (- No hidden fallback prompt. The CLI requires an explicit request.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 700 Td (- No free-form model protocol. The model must return JSON shaped as either a final) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70 685 Td (answer or a tool call.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 668 Td (- No full transcript replay forever. The runtime rebuilds a compact prompt from the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70 653 Td (request plus bounded tool history.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 636 Td (- No monolithic tool file. Each tool owns its schema and provider code.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 609 Td (3. The Smallest System That Works) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 587 Td (The runtime flow is:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 568 Td (- Step 1: The CLI parses the request and runtime options in src/main.ts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 551 Td (- Step 2: The agent loop builds a strict system prompt in src/agent.ts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 534 Td (- Step 3: The model can return only one of two JSON shapes: {"type":"final"} or) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70 519 Td ({"type":"tool"}.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 502 Td (- Step 4: If the model asks for a tool, the registry validates arguments with Zod, runs) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70 487 Td (the tool, and converts the result into structured success or failure output.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 470 Td (- Step 5: The structured tool result is fed back to the model as evidence.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 453 Td (- Step 6: An optional validation cycle checks the draft answer against the request and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70 438 Td (tool evidence before accepting it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 421 Td (- Step 7: The loop stops when a final answer is accepted or a step limit is reached.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 404 Td (This architecture is intentionally narrow. It avoids planning layers, memory systems,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 389 Td (multi-agent orchestration, and dynamic tool discovery because none of those are required) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 374 Td (for the current user outcome.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 345 Td (4. Architecture Diagram) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54 323 Td (The runtime boundary looks like this:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 498 28 Td (Page 2 of 5) Tj ET
